It would be really useful to have a distinction between grade/test cells (which have actual tests in them) and cells that just need to not change. For example, in many of my assignments we have people implement a function, and then call it on a particular set of data that's defined inline in the notebook; then they have to interpret their results. I don't want people to change the cells where we define that inline data, because that will make things a nightmare for the grader, but I also don't want to mark them as grade cells because (1) they're not worth any points, and (2) it will screw up `nbgrader validate --invert` (because those cells always pass).

In every other respect, these cells would act just like grade cells: `nbgrader validate` would warn students about changing these cells, and they would get overwritten from the saved version in the database when the autograder is run.

@ellisonbg what do you think? This would add more complexity, but would also make things a lot easier. I find myself on almost every assignment wishing that we had a cell type like this.

Apologies for cross-posting from [here](https://github.com/jupyter/help/issues/149), but I'm not sure there's that much traffic through there.

